A live recording from the Memphis Repertory Orchestra's debut CD release concert on March 2, 2013. The concert was given in the brand new Nancy Crosby Theater in the Salvation Army Kroc Center in Memphis, TN. 
Will Haapaniemi - Violin
William R. Langley - Music Director

http://memphisreporchestra.bandcamp.com
http://memphisreporchestra.com
tracks.title: Night on Bald Mountain

user.description:
"Shaping the Next Generation of Orchestral Musicians"

When you think of Memphis, TN, you most likely think of its profound musical influence--specifically in soul and blues. Memphis is home to some of the world's premiere music history sites: Stax, Sun Studios, Beale Street, Graceland, Ardent Studios, the list goes on and on. In 2011, The Memphis Repertory Orchestra (MRO) began working on adding its name to that legendary list.

When the MRO formed under the leadership of William Langley, they wanted to put Memphis on the music map, again, but this time by distinguishing the city as a great new epicenter for classical music. While the city already plays host to a fantastic Symphony, which performs in a state-of-the-art concert hall, the MRO strives to reach an even broader audience by getting the younger generation involved in the process, especially students.

The orchestra is comprised of local undergraduate and high school students alongside area amateur and professional musicians, all working on a volunteer basis. Founded by Mr. Langley, then a freshman college music student, with the support of colleagues, the intent of the orchestra was to offer student musicians an opportunity to perform and rehearse the way a professional orchestra does - with only a few intense rehearsals and then a concert.

Langley's philanthropy also extends into the orchestra's business model. The orchestra has been performing regularly for the Memphis community in the Buckman Performing Arts Center (originally performing in the famous Cooper/Young district of Memphis), but free-of charge.

tracks.caption: Uma impressionante interpretação dos Cantos e danças da morte, de Mussorgsky .
tracks.description:
Modest Mussorgsky (Orch. Dmitri Shostakovich) - Songs and Dances of Death (1875/77 - 1962)
1. Lullaby (Колыбельная) (14 April 1875) (in F-sharp minor–A minor)
2. Serenade (Серенада) (11 May 1875) (in E minor–E-flat minor)
3. Trepak (Трепак) (17 February 1875) (in D minor)
The Field Marshal (Полководец) (5 June 1877) (in E-flat minor–D minor)
Lyrics by Arseny Golenishchev-Kutuzov
Soloist - Patricio Alvarez
Orquestra Sinfônica Municipal de Campinas
Conductor - Victor Hugo Toro
Live recording - Teatro Municipal Castro Mendes - Campinas SP - Brazil - June 29 2024
Illustration - Aleksandr Jounev
tracks.title: Modest Mussorgsky (Orch. Shostakovich) - Songs and Dances of Death - Alvarez - Toro- Campinas - 2019
